ABAKALIKI – Frontline APC presidential contender and Governor of Ebonyi State, David Umahi, on Sunday met with the Chairman of Nigeria Governors Forum who is also an APC presidential aspirant, Kayode Fayemi in his Abuja residence. The meeting was not unconnected to the directive of President Muhammadu Buhari, to all aspirants to consult and come up with an acceptable candidate that would fly the flag of the party for the 2023 presidential election. Governor Umahi is the only sitting Governor from South East who is vying to become the candidate of the party. -Advertisement- Both Governors agreed on aligning with the decision of President Buhari and the party – that whosoever they finally present as the presidential candidate, they would give their full support. Governor Umahi noted that in the interest of peace, equity, fairness, and national cohesion, it woild be most acceptable that Mr. President and the Party considered narrowing the search by choosing any of the aspirants from South East with an assurance that all other aspirants from the zone would support the chosen one.